H0.text: Star clusters are groups of stars that are smaller than a galaxy.

H1.text: Milky Way are groups of stars called that are smaller than a galaxy.

H2.text: Nebuli are groups of stars that are smaller than a galaxy.

H3.text: Constellations are groups of stars that are smaller than a galaxy.

A4.text: A star cluster is a group of stars, predominantly within a galaxy, held together by self-gravitation.

A5.text: Globular clusters, with more members and more mass, remain intact for far longer and the globular clusters observed are usually billions of years old.
